sql:
SELECT AVG(revision_count) AS average_revisions
FROM (
  SELECT content_id, COUNT(revision_id) AS revision_count
  FROM revisions
  GROUP BY content_id
) AS revision_counts;

SELECT title, live 
FROM content 
WHERE content_id IN (SELECT content_id FROM content_tags WHERE tag_name = 'popular');

external_knowledge:
- Revisions refer to changes made to content items; 
- Average revision count refers to the total revisions divided by the number of content items; 
- The query aims to rank content items based on their revision activity.
